  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="4756424">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/4756424/" class="title-link">思想实验：一种神奇的思维工具</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-4756424"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/3620012/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u3620012-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/3620012/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">子炎</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2011-03-05"
      class="main-meta">2011-03-05 15:13:53</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_4756424_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                   在谈论思想实验之前，我不妨先提一个问题：假如，不给任何工具，要你证明宇宙究竟是有限还是无限，你打算怎么做？ 在2000年前，古罗马哲学家卢克莱修是这么做的：他问，假如宇宙是有限的，你走到宇宙尽头，使劲掷出一支矛，那会出现什么？只有两种情况，弹回来，或者继续往前...

